gomodel:SYNGO_2239  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" , "Rationale: Fig.S1: \"Immunogold labeling for endogenous Kv4.2 showing its\nexpression in CA1 spines. ... Most\ngold particles were detected in postsynaptic spines but not directly in the\npostsynaptic density.\"\n\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: \"Supplementary Figure 1. Immunogold labeling for endogenous Kv4.2 showing its\nexpression in CA1 spines. Antibodies against Kv4.2 (K57/1, 5.5 ug/ml) were\nlabeled with 10 nm gold and applied in sections of the hippocampal CA1 stratum\nradiatum of two P37 male Sprague-Dawley rats, after (Petralia et al., 2005).\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9425-2935" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
